Unit.$comment: The name or number of the unit within a site

Floor.$comment: To identify, by name or number, of the floor in a building, as part of an address.

Plot.$comment: A textual description of a small piece of land on which this address is located.

BuildingNumber.$comment: The number of a building or house on a street of this address.

BuildingName.$comment: The name of the building or house on a street of this address

ComplexName.$comment: Where the address is within a complex, scheme or site, the name of the complex

StreetName.$comment: Name of a street or thoroughfare

CitySubDivision.$comment: A text string identifying a division of a city, for example a local authority area, district or borough.

CityName.$comment: The name of the city, town or village of this address.

CountrySubentityName.$comment: The name that identifies the territorial division (a chief unit of local administration) of a country, as part of an address, For example a UK County, or a US State etc.

CountrySubentityCode.$comment: The code for the administrative subdivision of a country. For example, in the US this is state abbreviation.

Country.$comment:
To provide country information related to this address.

The country of the address (not the country code)

PostalCode.$comment: The identifier for one or more properties according to the postal service of that country; a group of letters and/or numbers added to the postal address to assist in the sorting of mail. E.g. UK postcode or US zip code

GooglePlaceID.$comment: Google Place IDs uniquely identify a place in the Google Places database and on Google Maps. It is a variable length string containing alphanumeric and some symbolic characters. For more information, see https://developers.google.com/places/place-id

items.$comment: Geographic coordinate of longitude, easting or other orthogonally equivalent measure in the reference system indicated by CoordinateReferenceSystemCode, as a decimal fraction (+-180.000000). Positives are east and negatives are west.

Geographic coordinate of latitude, northting or other orthogonally equivalent measure in the reference system indicated by CoordinateReferenceSystemCode, as a decimal fraction (+-90.000000). Positives are north and negatives are south.

CoordinateReferenceSystemCode.$comment:
The common Code given in the EPSG (European Petroleum Survey Group) Geodetic Parameter Registry. The Registry is a structured repository of data required to:
a) identify coordinates such that those coordinates describe position unambiguously through a coordinate reference system (CRS) definition; and
b) define transformations and conversions that allow coordinates to be changed from one CRS to another CRS.
See also: http://www.epsg.org/Geodetic.html

items.$comment: Height above the Elevation Reference defined by the Elevation Reference System.
Indicates a standard frame of reference on the earth for vertical elevation.

IntervalTypeCode.$comment: Specifies what the FrequencyCode attribute applies to - for example an "hourly" frequency code with an interval count of "10,000" could mean 10,000 elapsed hours or 10,000 operating hours.

FrequencyCode.$comment: The time period used to measure the interval between events

IntervalCount.$comment: The number of intervals (specified by Frequency Code) between events. If this is omitted, it is assumed to be 1. For example, if the Frequency code is "70" (quarterly) and this attribute is omitted, it is assumed that the event occurs every quarter, where as if this attribute was present with a value of 3, it would mean the event occurs once every 3 quarters.

items.$comment: Optionally specifies which day or days of the week this event should be occur on. If multiple days are selected, it is understood that the event occurs on *every* day. For example, a frequency of weekly and day of the week codes for Tuesday and Thursday would mean the event takes place on every Tuesday and every Thursday.

StartDate.$comment: The date (and time if appropriate) of the first instance, inclusive.

CurrencyCode.$comment: The currency of this monetary amount

Amount.$comment: The amount of money in the specified currency

Filename.$comment: The file system name of the file that is attached - used as the default or suggested name if the file is 'saved'.

AsOfDate.$comment: The last date for which the information in the attachment has been verified to be current. Also the effective date, for example the date a photograph was taken.

CreationDateTime.$comment: Date and time a document or attachment was created

URI.$comment: If the attachment is available via a link, the uniform resource identifier (URI) of the attachment. This may be a public link, or a private link to which the recipient has access.

Title.$comment: Title or caption for the attached file or document

EmbeddedFileBinaryObject.$comment: An electronic representation of the attachment encoded into text using Base64 content encoding. For more details on this encoding, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Base64

CopyrightNotices.$comment: Text description of any legal or copyright notices that may apply to the file in question

Years.$comment: The number of complete years in this duration. When calculating an end date by adding this duration to a start date, the number of years are added first, before any other duration attributes.

Months.$comment: The number of complete months in this duration. When calculating an end date by adding this duration to a start date, the number of years are added first, then the number of months, before any other duration attributes.

Days.$comment: The number of complete days in this duration. When calculating an end date by adding this duration to a start date, the number of years are added first, then the months, then weeks, then days, before any other duration attributes.

Name.$comment:
The full name of this organization

To specify any name related to this organization.

Full.$comment: A string of characters providing a name or set of names by which this person is known

Given.$comment: Name or names, usually given to a person by his/her parents at birth, also known as forename, first name or Christian name.

Family.$comment: The name a person shares with members of his/her family, also known as surname.

FamilyPrefix.$comment: The textual description of any prefix that precedes this person's family name such as van, von etc. (Fred Van Blommestein).

Initials.$comment: Generally in the form of a set of the initial letters of the Given and Middle names, optionally space-delimited.

Title.$comment: The textual description of any title associated with a specific person such as Dr.,  Ir. etc.

Middle.$comment: Name or names, usually given to a person by his/her parents at birth, other than the first name.

Name.$comment: The name of the Party. This is the Organization name, or the individual's full name. If a Partnership, then list four partners' names. If the named Party is described in the agreement as acting as Nominee or trustee for another Entity then the Name of the other Entity should be included here. For example: "John Smith acting as trustee for the PISCES Pension Fund".

ID.$comment: The actual reference number or string used to identify a particular entity in a system or process.

Description.$comment: An optional description for the reference, or more detail about this reference or who has allocated the reference. For example, this can be used to specify that this reference is a bar code attached to some physical component.

AllocatedBy.$comment: An identifier of the organization and/or system that allocated this identifier - this could be the name of the organization and/or system or something that identifies the specific instance of a system or database where the ID originated.

Name.$comment: The name of the asset where this is not implicit from the type.

InstallationDate.$comment: The date on which the asset was installed

WarrantyStartDate.$comment: The date from which the warranty starts

OmniClassTypeCode.$comment: The classification of this asset, per the OmniClass table 23 code list

UniclassProductTypeCode.$comment: The classification of this asset, per the Uniclass Product code list

UniclassSystemTypeCode.$comment: The classification of this asset, per the Uniclass System code list

UniclassElementFunctionTypeCode.$comment: The classification of this asset, per the Uniclass Element / Function code list

UniclassSpaceLocationTypeCode.$comment: The classification of this asset, per the Uniclass Space / Location code list

Name.$comment: A brief description of the asset type, e.g. 'Passenger elevator'

Description.$comment: One or more phrases or sentences describing the asset type, e.g. Glass-enclosed 12-person passenger elevator with alternative access elevations

ModelNumber.$comment: The reference used by the manufacturer to distinguish between assets of this and other types and variants manufactured by them

QuantityUnitOfMeasurementCode.$comment: This is the unit of measurement used to state the area (eg metric or imperial; cubic or squared)

NominalLengthUnitOfMeasurementCode.$comment: This is the unit of measurement used to state the area (eg metric or imperial; cubic or squared)

NominalWidthUnitOfMeasurementCode.$comment: This is the unit of measurement used to state the area (eg metric or imperial; cubic or squared)

NominalHeightUnitOfMeasurementCode.$comment: This is the unit of measurement used to state the area (eg metric or imperial; cubic or squared)

items.$comment: A narrative description of this Space Grouping
The name of this Space Grouping - for example "Finance Neighborhood", "Lift Shaft" or "All fire refuge spaces"

SpaceLocationType.$comment: If applicable, the Uniclass Space/Location code that describes the type of this collection of Spaces

UnitNumber.$comment: The name (usually a number) that the unit is known by in the building.

items.$comment: A full description of this unit.

LeaseTenureType.$comment: The type of tenure/rent that this lease is subject to

Name.$comment: Formal Name. Eg Corporate Headquarters site

This name this building is known as in the context. This may be the actual building name (which can also be provided in the Address entity) or it may be a name for this building in some other context.

Name of Floor or Level within a building.  Includes all accessible levels of a building, including the roof level, mezzanines, interstitial spaces, basements, sub-basements and crawlspaces.   Description of floor or level, not abbreviated (e.g., basement, first-floor, mezzanine, roof, etc.); apply standards, not necessarily a VVL)

FloorNumber.$comment: This is the Floor Number e.g. -1, 0, 1. For floors that do not have a natural numeric label, this may be omitted, or interpolated between or around floors that do have numeric labels - for example the 'Ground Floor' maye be identified with number '0'.

SpaceName.$comment: An identification of the leased space.

SpaceDescription.$comment: An textual description of the leased space.

items.$comment: The property type as described by the Uniclass "Entity" table

SiteTypeCode.$comment: The type of this site using the Uniclass "Complex" table
